        "text": "*[Bug 19013] New: Incorrect computations in mood.test (and ansari.test?) in case of ties*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19013>\n\n            Bug ID: 19013\n           Summary: Incorrect computations in mood.test (and ansari.test?)\n                    in case of ties\n           Product: R\n           Version: R 4.5.x\n          Hardware: All\n                OS: All\n            Status: UNCONFIRMED\n          Severity: normal\n          Priority: P5\n         Component: Accuracy\n          Assignee: <mailto:R-core@R-project.org|R-core@R-project.org>\n          Reporter: <mailto:robert.schlicht@tu-dresden.de|robert.schlicht@tu-dresden.de>\n\nThe implementation of Mood's test for difference in scale parameters\n(src\/library\/stats\/R\/mood.test.R) seems to follow the reference\n<https:\/\/doi.org\/10.2307\/1266427>, but contains a sign error in the computation\nwith ties. Namely, the expression (N-S_{i}-S_{i-1})^2 from the article has been\nmistranslated as `(N - t) ^ 2` instead of (for example) `(N - 2*cumsum(t) + t)\n^ 2`. Only after correcting this,\n```\nd &lt;- data.frame(grp = factor(c(\"A\",\"A\",\"A\",\"B\",\"B\",\"B\")), y = c(3,2,3,4,1,5))\nmood.test(y ~ grp, data = d)\n```\nreturns the (presumably correct) p-value also returned by the following\nfunction from the `coin` package:\n```\ncoin::mood_test(y ~ grp, data = d,\n  ties.method = \"average-scores\", distribution = \"asymptotic\")\n```\n\nThe implementation of the Ansari-Bradley test\n(src\/library\/stats\/R\/ansari.test.R) appears to inconsistently combine mid-ranks\n(in `r &lt;- rank(c(x, y))`) with moment calculations for average scores as\nexplained in Hollander, Wolfe, Chicken, *Nonparametric Statistical Methods*\n(3rd ed., 2014), Chapter 5.1, in particular page 156. So the result of\n```\nansari.test(y ~ grp, data = d, exact = FALSE)\n```\ncorresponds to neither of:\n```\ncoin::ansari_test(y ~ grp, data = d,\n  ties.method = \"average-scores\", distribution = \"asymptotic\")\ncoin::ansari_test(y ~ grp, data = d,\n  ties.method = \"mid-ranks\", distribution = \"asymptotic\")\n```\nIn fact, the help page for `ansari.test` (section \"See Also\") points out the\ndifferent computations in `ansari_test`, although I am not sure it gives the\ncorrect reason.\n\nA final comment: The data in both Examples sections, taken from Example 5.1 in\nthe book (or ultimately <https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1093\/ajcp\/54.6.813>), look\nsuspiciously like paired samples that might not be ideal candidates for those\ntests; of course, this does not matter here.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
