                                "text": "robert.schlicht@tu-dresden.de",
                                "unsafe": true
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nThe implementation of Mood's test for difference in scale parameters\n(src\/library\/stats\/R\/mood.test.R) seems to follow the reference\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/doi.org\/10.2307\/1266427"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ", but contains a sign error in the computation\nwith ties. Namely, the expression (N-S_{i}-S_{i-1})^2 from the article has been\nmistranslated as "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "(N - t) ^ 2",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " instead of (for example) `(N - 2*cumsum(t) + t)\n^ 2`. Only after correcting this,"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "d <- data.frame(grp = factor(c(\"A\",\"A\",\"A\",\"B\",\"B\",\"B\")), y = c(3,2,3,4,1,5))\nmood.test(y ~ grp, data = d)\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "returns the (presumably correct) p-value also returned by the following\nfunction from the "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "coin",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " package:"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "coin::mood_test(y ~ grp, data = d,\n  ties.method = \"average-scores\", distribution = \"asymptotic\")\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nThe implementation of the Ansari-Bradley test\n(src\/library\/stats\/R\/ansari.test.R) appears to inconsistently combine mid-ranks\n(in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "r <- rank(c(x, y))",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") with moment calculations for average scores as\nexplained in Hollander, Wolfe, Chicken, "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Nonparametric Statistical Methods",
                                "style": {
                                    "bold": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n(3rd ed., 2014), Chapter 5.1, in particular page 156. So the result of"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "ansari.test(y ~ grp, data = d, exact = FALSE)\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "corresponds to neither of:"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "coin::ansari_test(y ~ grp, data = d,\n  ties.method = \"average-scores\", distribution = \"asymptotic\")\ncoin::ansari_test(y ~ grp, data = d,\n  ties.method = \"mid-ranks\", distribution = \"asymptotic\")\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "In fact, the help page for "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "ansari.test",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " (section \"See Also\") points out the\ndifferent computations in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "ansari_test",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ", although I am not sure it gives the\ncorrect reason.\n\nA final comment: The data in both Examples sections, taken from Example 5.1 in\nthe book (or ultimately "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1093\/ajcp\/54.6.813"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "), look\nsuspiciously like paired samples that might not be ideal candidates for those\ntests; of course, this does not matter here."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
