        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 19012] foreign::write.foreign() generates incorrect SAS INPUT statement for character variables*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19012>\n\nElin Waring (<mailto:elin.waring@gmail.com|elin.waring@gmail.com>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |elin.waring@gmail.com\n\n--- Comment #1 from Elin Waring (<mailto:elin.waring@gmail.com|elin.waring@gmail.com>) ---\nHaving a `$` after \"a\" is not needed because `a` is already defined as a\ncharacter by the `LENGTH` statement.  You don't need the `$` for `c` for the\nsame reason. \n\nThe `$` is not hurting anything but is poor SAS style, and it is confusing to\nhave it for one and not the other.  \n\nThis comment was dictate do me by <https:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/users\/4965549\/tom>.",
