        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 18989] Wishlist: provide conversion of POSIXlt time zone retaining sub-second accuracy*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=18989>\n\n--- Comment #5 from Martin Maechler (<mailto:maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch|maechler@stat.math.ethz.ch>) ---\n(In reply to Suharto Anggono from comment #4)\nI've committed such a `c.POSIXlt()` to R-devel, in svn r 89501  earlier today.\n\nFurther improvements wished for, notably, the main wish for keeping the full\nsubsecond accuracy in other POSIXlt methods which act via POSIXct, i.e.,\nconceptually\n```\n&lt;FUN&gt;.POSIXlt &lt;- function(x, &lt;more&gt;) \n   as.POSIXlt(&lt;FUN&gt;(as.POSIXct(x, &lt;more_1&gt;), &lt;more_2&gt;, x$sec)\n```\nhowever has not been done.\nR level code functions this *could* be done in are e.g.,\n`+.POSIXt`, `-.POSIXt` and `Ops.POSIXt` ... but certainly there are more.\nHence, this PR remains open.",
